text.section:
A tax authorized under this section shall:
be imposed and collected as county taxes are imposed and collected;
have the same priority rights as county taxes;
bear the same interest and penalties as county taxes; and
be treated the same as county taxes in every other respect.

section.section:
To calculate the net unexpended balance for each county, the Commission shall deduct, from its actual unexpended cash receipts from taxes collected under this section, an amount equal to the sum of:
the debt service for the next succeeding fiscal year on bonds issued by it and outstanding with respect to property acquired by it in the county;
the Commission's fixed obligations under contracts the first 6 months of the fiscal year;
the amounts credited to the Commission's self-insurance fund;
$200,000 with respect to Montgomery County; and
$150,000 with respect to Prince George's County.
